Docker 6/6 - container orchestration tools 

Kubernetes (k8) -> platform designed to automate an the deployment , scaling and operation of containers 

- K8 helps with container orchestration , auto scaling up/down and self healing 
- Needed when dealing with so many containers 
- It comes in when your managing a fleet of containers across different machines 

? Docker swarm vs Kubernetes 

Docker Swarm -> more simpler and docker native
- making it easy to turn on and off cluster
- Very lightweight as an orchestration tool 
- No autoscaling so manually have to with other tools 
- Limited to docker api as it’s native - like docker commands and services 

Kubernetes -> more complex with additional features
- More complicated to set up but is for large enterprise production scale environments
- More heavyweight as an orchestration tool 
- Has features like autoscaling and custom controls 
- K8 not limited to docker api / capabilities being more flexible and can integrate with different containers runtimes and has more features 

? Why should companies use orchestration tools 
- Handle the complexity for you 
- Ensure high availability 
- Increase efficiency so can worry about the actual app not the infrastructure 
- Enhances reliability 
- Optimise usage and provide resource utilisation though scaling as an example 
